==English==

===Noun===
'''[[extended]] [[playing]] [[time]]'''
# (''sports'') In a one-sided sporting contest, when [[junior varsity]] players (i.e., [[second-string|second]]- and [[third-string]] players) play a majority of the game.
:Usually done for one or more reasons, including to show [[sportsmanship]], to give younger players game experience and/or to keep first-string players from being injured needlessly in a game where the outcome has effectively been decided.
#: ''Once the No. 1 team football built an early 56-0 lead in the game against their weak opponents, the coach - wanting to spare the opponent further embarassment and sensing his own younger players needed experience - decided to give his reserves some well-deserved '''extended playing time'''.''